onumber \ 0=-9-12y
onumber \end{align} \] The third row, below the line, shows the difference between row 2 minus row 1. From the bottom row we can solve for y and then get the solution \(y^{*}\): \[  egin{align} -9-12y &amp; =0\ y^{*} &amp; =- rac{3}{4}
